cd $HOME	go home. 	
Cd ~/	Go home. Absolute path. 	
clear	clear the screen	
cd (name of a directory)	move to a specific directory	
man command	shows the operator’s manual for a command	
q	quit	return to command line
ls -lrth	additional information	
head	prints 10 lines of the file to the screen	head filename.fastq
tail	show last 10 lines of a file	tail filename.fastq
tail -n3	show the last 3 lines	tail -n3 filename.fastq
cat filename.fastq	prints the entire file to the screen	cat home/msm1094/gen711-811/shell_data/untrimmed_fastq
