^	search for the beginning of a line, e.g. ^@ = search for @ at the beginning of a line
-n 	adds the line numbers in a search command
grep -v "pattern" file.txt	reverse grep (exclude search term rather than include them)
ls | grep ‘something’	finds everything in the folder with ‘something’
